'''''Tournament Golf''''' is a 1988 video game published by [[Computer Sports Network]] for [[DOS]].

==Gameplay==
''Tournament Golf'' is a game in which using a modem, players could compete in a nationwide golf tournament each week.<ref name="CGW63"/> It is played using ''[[Mean 18]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.org/details/1990-04-compute-magazine/page/n67/mode/2up|title=Compute! Magazine Issue 119|date=April 27, 1990|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>

==Reception==
David S. Stevens reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "For those tired of competing against just the computer, CSN can provide plenty of stiff competition on some of the world's most challenging golf courses. That is something that neither family, time, nor ability would allow us to experience in 'the real world.'"<ref name="CGW63">{{cite magazine |last=Stevens |first=David S. |title=Linking Up for Tournament Golf |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=September 1989 |volume=1 |issue=63 |pages=38, 43}}</ref>

